The article announces that Gene B. Sperling, Director of the National Economic Council and Assistant to the President for Economic Policy, will be leaving the White House on January 1, 2014. President Obama will appoint Jeffrey Zients, former Acting Director of the Office of Management and Budget, as the new Director of the National Economic Council. President Obama praises Sperling for his work in helping the economy recover and making the tax code more fair. He also expresses gratitude to Sperling and his family for their service. President Obama is confident that Zients, with his business experience and leadership skills, will continue to provide strong economic policy leadership. The article also provides a biography of Jeffrey Zients, highlighting his previous positions and business experience.